                   -0.7 kpc. The proper motion of Sgr B2 relative to Sgr
                   A* suggests that Sgr B2 is ≈0.13 kpc nearer than
                   the Galactic center, assuming a low-eccentricity
                   Galactic orbit.},
  doi =           {10.1088/0004-637X/705/2/1548},
}

@article{Boehle2016a,
  author =        {{Boehle}, A. and {Ghez}, A.~M. and {Sch{\"o}del}, R. and
