  abstract =      {In this paper, we present a dust emission map of the
                   starless core TMC-1C taken at 2100 mum. Along with
                   maps at 160, 450, 850, and 1200 mum, we study the
                   dust emissivity spectral index from the
                   (sub)millimeter spectral energy distribution, and
                   find that it is close to the typically assumed value
                   of beta = 2. We also map the dust temperature and
                   column density in TMC-1C, and find that at the
                   position of the dust peak (AV ~ 50) the
